# Git commit messages

When creating commits for this repo (including suggested messages), match the style in `git log --oneline`:

- **One short subject line** only, unless the user explicitly asks for a body.
- **Roughly two to six words** is typical; keep it tight.
- **No trailing period** on the subject.
- **Capitalization**: Title Case phrases (`Login throttling`, `Main page`) or **lowercase with hyphens** for compact feature labels (`playlists-table`, `playlist.userId`) — both appear in history; pick whichever fits the change.
- Optional **`Add …`** prefix is fine when it stays short (`Add Users page`).

## Examples (good)

- `Login throttling`
- `Main page`
- `Genre delete`
- `Add Users page`
- `playlist.userId`

## Examples (avoid unless asked)

- Long single-line subjects that read like full sentences with clauses.
- Conventional-commit prefixes (`feat:`, `fix:`) — not used in this repo’s history.
